title: Grateful Dead Live at Beacon Theatre on 1976-06-14
lineage: SBD DAT > TASCAM DA-20 (spdif out) -> Apogee Wide Eye spdif innterconnect and Audience (shnid:10917) Source: Sony TC 153 Sony SCM 99A Mikes > Cassette  x 2 > DAT > Tascam Da-p1 dat @48khz > Sek'd Prodif+ card (48>44.1khz) > Sek'd Red Roaster (fades, edits*) > Cdwav (splits) > Mkw
description:
Set 1

Cold Rain & Snow, Mama Tried, Row Jimmy, Cassidy, Brown Eyed Women, Big River, Might As Well, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Tennessee Jed, Playin' In The Band

Set 2

The Wheel, Samson & Delilah, High Time, The Music Never Stopped, Crazy Fingers-> Dancin' In The Streets-> Cosmic Charlie-> Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower-> Around & Around, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: - Excellent! Great show, beautiful sound treatment. Is there a corrected audience recording available? The one you're using is obviously speed-corrected at least, unlike the only one currently present here on the archive.

Great, tight, funky show! Sounds great too. Super fun show to groove out too. Absolutely beautiful Crazy Fingers (maybe my favorite!) and a really surprisingly good Cosmic Charlie. Awesome Matrix, love hearing the crowd get hyped. Super fun. Check it out!
